Connect is a web application developed using the MERN (MongoDB, Express.js, React, Node.js) stack to facilitate communication and mentorship between aspiring students, professors, and industry professionals. 
The platform is designed to help students connect with mentors to foster learning, guidance, and professional growth.
1.User Authentication & Authorization
   Secure user authentication using JWT (JSON Web Tokens) for both mentors and students.
   Role-based access control to differentiate between students, professors, and professionals.
   Encrypted password storage using bcrypt to ensure data security.
2. Profile Creation and Management
  Users can create personalized profiles with relevant information like areas of interest, expertise, and goals.
3. Mentor-Student Matching
  Implemented a feature that matches students with mentors based on shared interests and fields of study.
4. Communication Tools
  Real-time messaging between mentors and students using Socket.io for seamless communication.
5.Discussion Forum
  A community space where students and mentors can post questions, share knowledge, and discuss academic or career topics.
6. Data Storage and Management
   User data, session details, messages, and reviews are stored securely in a MongoDB database.
   Efficient querying and data retrieval using Mongoose ORM.

Technologies Used

Frontend:
React.js (Functional components with hooks)
React Router for navigation
Axios for API calls
CSS/Bootstrap for styling

Backend:
Node.js and Express.js for building the API
MongoDB and Mongoose for database management
JWT for user authentication
Bcrypt for password hashing
Socket.io for real-time communication
